SA recorded wins over France (14-7), Kenya (35-10) and Canada (26-7) to advance to the last eight despite fielding an injury-depleted team.The Blitzboks have never won the Hong Kong title the most prestigious of the 10 tournaments on the HSBC World Sevens Series.After a slow start against France, who kicked deep to keep the Blitzboks pinned back, the youthful team clicked in their last two pool matches.The Blitzboks dominated breakdowns and used their smothering defence to frustrate Kenya and Canada. They also relied heavily on veteran Cecil Afrika, playing in his 50th World Series tournament, to pull the strings.By reaching the last eight SA has now won 36 of 39 matches this season, which includes four of the six tournaments of the season.